cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper proposes a deep learning framework for hyperspectral image classification, which involves both spectral and spatial feature learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Among these, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on deep learning-based feature extraction and classification, which are core topics in both fields. The use of recurrent and convolutional operators also suggests a potential connection to cs.NE, while the application to hyperspectral image analysis could relate to cs.IR.
